{"types":[{"section":"\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[nightmare]]\n#: {{ant|fr|rêve}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Je n'ai pas pu dormir hier soir parce que j'ai fait trop de '''cauchemars.'''|t=I couldn't sleep last night because I had too many '''nightmares.'''}}\n#: {{ux|fr|C'était un rêve ou un '''cauchemar?'''|t=Was it a dream or a '''nightmare?'''}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Il a remué toute la nuit, je crois qu'il a fait des '''cauchemars.'''|t=He was tossing and turning all night, I think [that] he had '''nightmares.'''}}\n#: {{ux|fr|J'ai eu un accident ce matin! Je vais bien mais ça a été un vrai '''cauchemar!'''|t=I had an accident this morning! I'm okay but it was a true '''nightmare!'''}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{m|fr|cauchemar|Cauchemar}} is often used with the transitive verb {{m|fr|[[faire]]}} [to [[do]]/to [[make]]] instead of the verb {{m|fr|[[avoir]]|}} [to [[have]]]. {{m|fr|[[faire|Faire]] un '''cauchemar'''}} = ''to [[have]]'' a '''nightmare'''.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|fr\n|cauchemardant\n|cauchemardement\n|cauchemarder\n|cauchemardesque\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|bg|кошмар|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|en|cauchemar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|eo|koŝmaro|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|et|košmaar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|io|koshmaro|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lt|košmaras|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mk|кошмар|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|koszmar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ro|coșmar|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|ru|кошмар|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sh|-|bor=1}}\n*: {{desc|sh|košmar|sclb=1}}\n*: {{desc|sh|кошмар|sclb=1}}\n* {{desc|uk|кошмар|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|vo|kojmar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|yi|קאָשמאַר|bor=1}}\n\n","alt":[],"syn":[],"type":"noun","forms":[{"g":"m","n":"s"}],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\">cauchemar</strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"gender\"><abbr title=\"masculine gender\">m</abbr></span> (<i>plural</i> <b class=\"Latn form-of lang-fr p-form-of\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/cauchemars#French\" title=\"cauchemars\">cauchemars</a></b>)</span>\n</p><ol><li><a href=\"/wiki/nightmare\" title=\"nightmare\">nightmare</a>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"nyms antonym\"><span class=\"defdate\">Antonym:</span> <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/r%C3%AAve#French\" title=\"rêve\">rêve</a></span></span></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Je n'ai pas pu dormir hier soir parce que j'ai fait trop de <b>cauchemars.</b></i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">I couldn't sleep last night because I had too many <b>nightmares.</b></span></dd></dl></div></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">C'était un rêve ou un <b>cauchemar?</b></i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">Was it a dream or a <b>nightmare?</b></span></dd></dl></div></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Il a remué toute la nuit, je crois qu'il a fait des <b>cauchemars.</b></i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">He was tossing and turning all night, I think [that] he had <b>nightmares.</b></span></dd></dl></div></dd>\n<dd><div class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">J'ai eu un accident ce matin! Je vais bien mais ça a été un vrai <b>cauchemar!</b></i><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">I had an accident this morning! I'm okay but it was a true <b>nightmare!</b></span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></li></ol><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Usage_notes\">Usage notes</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=cauchemar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: Usage notes\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><p><i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><strong class=\"selflink\">Cauchemar</strong></i> is often used with the transitive verb <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/faire#French\" title=\"faire\">faire</a></i> [to <a href=\"/wiki/do\" title=\"do\">do</a>/to <a href=\"/wiki/make\" title=\"make\">make</a>] instead of the verb <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir#French\" title=\"avoir\">avoir</a></i> [to <a href=\"/wiki/have\" title=\"have\">have</a>]. <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/faire#French\" title=\"faire\">Faire</a> un <b>cauchemar</b></i> = <i>to <a href=\"/wiki/have\" title=\"have\">have</a></i> a <b>nightmare</b>.\n</p><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Derived_terms\">Derived terms</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=cauchemar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Derived terms\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><div class=\"list-switcher-wrapper\"><div class=\"term-list columns-bg\"><ul><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/cauchemardant#French\" title=\"cauchemardant\">cauchemardant</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/cauchemardement#French\" title=\"cauchemardement\">cauchemardement</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/cauchemarder#French\" title=\"cauchemarder\">cauchemarder</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/cauchemardesque#French\" title=\"cauchemardesque\">cauchemardesque</a></span></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Descendants\">Descendants</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=cauchemar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Descendants\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><ul><li><span class=\"desc-arr\" title=\"borrowed\">→</span> Bulgarian: <span class=\"Cyrl\" lang=\"bg\"><a href=\"/wiki/%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%88%D0%BC%D0%B0%D1%80#Bulgarian\" title=\"кошмар\">кошмар</a></span> <span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">(</span><span lang=\"bg-La